    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-07-04T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-07-04T08:00:00-05:00" n="632"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d632">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6131/552: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_GSE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grummon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-07-04T16:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 4, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 4—11:34 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>363. Department’s 73, June 27, 4 p.m. I discussed the renewal of the commercial
                    agreement with <persName corresp="#p_PVP1">Potemkin</persName> yesterday who
                    said that he would consult with the Commissariat for Foreign Trade and inform
                    the Embassy promptly of the Soviet Government’s point of view. He stated that
                        <persName corresp="#p_UKA1">Umansky</persName> had discussed the matter with
                    the Secretary and he thought also with the President prior to his departure on
                    leave. He expressed himself as in agreement as to the desirability of dealing
                    with the matter promptly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grummon</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
